(698, 39, 'admin', '“Decarbonising Food Systems: Opportunities for a Concerned ASEAN”', '', '', '“decarbonising-food-systems-opportunities-for-a-concerned-asean”', 'N', 'N', 'N', '<h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"font-family: Roboto, \"Open Sans\"; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 22px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.35; display: inline;\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; overflow-wrap: break-word; font-weight: bold;\">EXECUTIVE SUMMARY</strong></h3><p style=\"font-family: Roboto, \"Open Sans\"; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\"></p><ul class=\"wp-block-list\" style=\"font-family: Roboto, \"Open Sans\"; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\"><li style=\"margin: 0px 0px 10px 15px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; overflow-wrap: break-word;\">The Paris Agreement under the United Nations Framework Convention on Climate Change (UNFCCC) has set a goal to limit global temperature increase to 1.5 °C above pre-industrial levels. To achieve this goal, greenhouse gas (GHG) emissions would have to be drastically reduced and countries should target a net zero condition by 2050.</li></ul><ul class=\"wp-block-list\" style=\"font-family: Roboto, \"Open Sans\"; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\"><li style=\"margin: 0px 0px 10px 15px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; overflow-wrap: break-word;\">In response to the Paris Agreement, many countries have submitted Nationally Determined Contributions (NDCs) to reduce GHGs in specific sectors, such as the agrifood sector, by setting target dates to achieve net zero.</li></ul><ul class=\"wp-block-list\" style=\"font-family: Roboto, \"Open Sans\"; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\"><li style=\"margin: 0px 0px 10px 15px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; overflow-wrap: break-word;\">Food system decarbonisation is one of the main pathways chosen by ASEAN Member States (AMS) to meet their NDCs. Concurrent with this is the transformation of food systems from high-emission, carbon energy-intensive systems to low-carbon emission systems with improved resilience, farmer livelihoods and environmental health.</li></ul><ul class=\"wp-block-list\" style=\"font-family: Roboto, \"Open Sans\"; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\"><li style=\"margin: 0px 0px 10px 15px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; overflow-wrap: break-word;\">Many tested approaches, practices and technologies are available to AMS, but their adoption faces barriers and requires incentives for small farmers to come on board. Agrifood sub-sectors like rice, oil palm, livestock and forestry offer great opportunities for early impact decarbonisation.</li></ul><ul class=\"wp-block-list\" style=\"font-family: Roboto, \"Open Sans\"; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\"><li style=\"margin: 0px 0px 10px 15px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; overflow-wrap: break-word;\">The impact of decarbonisation as a net zero tool can be accelerated through joint action among AMS facilitated by ASEAN, such as a Regional Decarbonisation Roadmap, regulatory harmonisation, as well as knowledge and technology sharing.</li></ul><ul class=\"wp-block-list\" style=\"font-family: Roboto, \"Open Sans\"; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\"><li style=\"margin: 0px 0px 10px 15px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; overflow-wrap: break-word;\">Decarbonisation in food systems is not about one solution in one part of the system but about transforming the whole system to be low-carbon, making it resilient to climate change, nutritionally adequate, environmentally sustainable and economically inclusive.</li></ul><p style=\"font-family: Roboto, \"Open Sans\"; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\"><em style=\"font-family: sans-serif;\">* Paul Teng is Visiting Senior Fellow at the Climate Change in Southeast Asia Programme at ISEAS – Yusof Ishak Institute, Singapore. He played a key role supporting the ASEAN Secretariat in developing the Food, Agriculture & Forestry Sectoral Plan 2026-2030.</em></p><p style=\"font-family: Roboto, \"Open Sans\"; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">ISEAS Perspective 2025/93, 20 November 2025</p><p class=\"download-pdf\" style=\"font-family: Roboto, \"Open Sans\"; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; display: flex; justify-content: center; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\"><a rel=\"noopener nofollow\" href=\"https://www.iseas.edu.sg/wp-content/uploads/2025/10/ISEAS_Perspective_2025_93.pdf\" style=\"color: rgb(255, 255, 255); margin: 0px; padding: 8px 18px; font-size: 12px; vertical-align: baseline; background: rgb(17, 69, 117); text-transform: uppercase;\">Download PDF Version</a></p><h3 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"font-family: Roboto, \"Open Sans\"; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 22px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.35; display: inline;\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; overflow-wrap: break-word; font-weight: bold;\">BACKGROUND</strong></h3><p style=\"font-family: Roboto, \"Open Sans\"; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\"></p><p style=\"font-family: Roboto, \"Open Sans\"; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">The landmark Paris Agreement[1] of 2015 provided the impetus for countries “to limit the temperature increase to 1.5°C above pre-industrial level” by the end of the century. Greenhouse gas (GHG) emissions from food systems are considered a major cause of temperature rise.</p><p style=\"font-family: Roboto, \"Open Sans\"; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">Food systems[2] include agriculture and supply chains to bring food to consumers. Globally, food systems account for 25–30% of total GHG emissions,[3] made up of carbon dioxide (CO₂) from farming practices like straw burning and fossil fuel use, methane (CH₄) from livestock and rice paddies, and nitrous oxide (N₂O) from synthetic fertilisers. Southeast Asia contributes only a fraction of global GHGs, at about 5.73%,[4] but, as will be discussed later, there are strong reasons for Southeast Asian countries to be concerned and to take action.</p><p style=\"font-family: Roboto, \"Open Sans\"; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">All ASEAN Member[5] States (AMS) have subsequently introduced their Nationally Determined Contributions (NDCs) and proclaimed net-zero emission targets for their agrifood sectors, mostly by mid-21<span style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 10.5px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; overflow-wrap: break-word; top: -0.5em; line-height: 0; position: relative;\">st</span> century (see Table 1). A common approach is to aim for a “net-zero” [6] economy by a specific year. To reach net-zero, a balance between anthropogenic GHG emissions and removals must be achieved using decarbonisation as a pathway.</p><p style=\"font-family: Roboto, \"Open Sans\"; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">Decarbonisation is the process of reducing and eventually eliminating greenhouse gas (GHG) emissions associated with the production, processing, transportation, consumption, and disposal of food,[7] i.e. in food systems. Decarbonising food systems includes preserving carbon sinks by stopping deforestation and promoting sustainable land use through conserving forests, peatlands, and healthy soils.</p><p style=\"font-family: Roboto, \"Open Sans\"; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">Without addressing emissions from food systems, climate action is incomplete, and it would be impossible to meet the Paris Agreement goals. A 2024 FAO analysis shows that around 91% of country NDCs include agrifood systems in mitigation, and 94% include them for adaptation.[8]Top food exporting countries,[9] such as the U.S.A., U.K., Germany, China, France, the Netherlands and Canada, have included food system decarbonisation in their NDCs. Decarbonisation is therefore a climate mitigation strategy and the focus of the NDCs.[10]</p><p style=\"font-family: Roboto, \"Open Sans\"; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">Decarbonisation can also be viewed as climate action[11] applied to transform food systems from the current high carbon, high GHG emission food systems into low-emission, sustainable systems.[12]</p><p style=\"font-family: Roboto, \"Open Sans\"; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">At the recent ASEAN Third Task Force Meeting: Finalising the Strategic Framework for Food, Agriculture, and Forestry (FAF) held on 30 June to 3 July 2025, in Nha Trang, Viet Nam, decarbonisation of food systems emerged as a major point for action over the next five years.</p><p style=\"font-family: Roboto, \"Open Sans\"; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\">This Perspective explores what is involved in decarbonisation, discusses the options available and challenges faced, and suggests action to take at the regional level to make decarbonisation a significant contributor to reducing GHG missions and consequently global warming.</p><h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\" style=\"font-family: Roboto, \"Open Sans\"; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 18px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; color: rgb(51, 51, 51); font-weight: bold; line-height: 1.35; display: inline;\"><strong style=\"margin: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; vertical-align: baseline; background: transparent; overflow-wrap: break-word; font-weight: bold;\">Table 1: AMS NDCs and Decarbonisation Action as of 2024</strong></h4><p style=\"font-family: Roboto, \"Open Sans\"; margin-right: 0px; margin-bottom: 25px; margin-left: 0px; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; line-height: 1.7; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\"></p><figure class=\"wp-block-table\" style=\"margin-bottom: 0px; font-family: Roboto, \"Open Sans\"; padding: 0px; border: 0px; outline: 0px; font-size: 14px; vertical-align: baseline; background-image: initial; background-position: initial; background-size: initial; background-repeat: initial; background-attachment: initial; background-origin: initial; background-clip: initial; overflow-wrap: break-word; overflow-x: auto; color: rgb(51, 51, 51);\"><table class=\"has-fixed-layout\" style=\"border-spacing: 0px; width: 717.5px; margin-bottom: 20px; table-layout: fixed;\"><tbody><tr><td style=\"border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; padding: 0.5em; word-break: break-word;\">ASEAN MEMBER STATE</td><td style=\"border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; padding: 0.5em; word-break: break-word;\">NDC DECLARATION</td><td style=\"border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; padding: 0.5em; word-break: break-word;\">GHG EMISSIONS GOALS</td><td style=\"border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; padding: 0.5em; word-break: break-word;\">FOOD SYSTEM DECARBONISATION</td></tr><tr><td style=\"border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; padding: 0.5em; word-break: break-word;\">Brunei Darussalam</td><td style=\"border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; padding: 0.5em; word-break: break-word;\">2020</td><td style=\"border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; padding: 0.5em; word-break: break-word;\">Net‑zero by 2050</td><td style=\"border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; padding: 0.5em; word-break: break-word;\">No sector‑specific mitigation actions</td></tr><tr><td style=\"border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; padding: 0.5em; word-break: break-word;\">Cambodia</td><td style=\"border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; padding: 0.5em; word-break: break-word;\">2020</td><td style=\"border-width: 1px; border-style: solid; padding: 0.5em; word-break: break